A taxi boss (39) died after he was shot multiple times in the head and back at his home on Old Inanda Road, Verulam, on Monday evening. According to Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa), they received multiple calls from residents in the area reporting the shooting. “On arrival, a man was located lying... in the yard. He was bleeding extensively from gunshot wounds to his head and back.” He died at the scene, Rusa said. According to a witness, a white VW Polo sedan stopped on the main road outside the property. “A lone gunman alighted from the vehicle and ran into the yard. He fired multiple shots before he sped off in the direction of Trenance Park. Six spent 9mm cartridges were recovered on scene,” Rusa said. The motive for the shooting has not been confirmed.